From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: suckbluefrog <suckbluefrog@proton.me>
Date: Mon, 1 Jun 2026 05:25:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] video_core: guard KosmicKrisp Vulkan driver ID

Eden v0.2.0 references VK_DRIVER_ID_MESA_KOSMICKRISP, but the Vulkan
headers currently packaged for zen3 do not define that newer enum yet.
Keep the friendly driver name when newer headers are available while
allowing the package to build against the existing headers.

Signed-off-by: suckbluefrog <suckbluefrog@proton.me>
---
 src/video_core/vulkan_common/vulkan_wrapper.cpp | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/video_core/vulkan_common/vulkan_wrapper.cpp b/src/video_core/vulkan_common/vulkan_wrapper.cpp
index 3e09960dc..fa2436967 100644
--- a/src/video_core/vulkan_common/vulkan_wrapper.cpp
+++ b/src/video_core/vulkan_common/vulkan_wrapper.cpp
@@ -1059,8 +1059,10 @@ std::string GetDriverName(VkPhysicalDeviceDriverProperties driver) {
         return "PVR";
     case VK_DRIVER_ID_MESA_HONEYKRISP:
         return "HoneyKrisp";
+#ifdef VK_DRIVER_ID_MESA_KOSMICKRISP
     case VK_DRIVER_ID_MESA_KOSMICKRISP:
         return "KosmicKrisp";
+#endif
     case VK_DRIVER_ID_GGP_PROPRIETARY:
     case VK_DRIVER_ID_COREAVI_PROPRIETARY:
     case VK_DRIVER_ID_JUICE_PROPRIETARY:
-- 
